filecopy - copies file from source to destination

Description:
The 'filecopy' command copies a file from the specified source path to the destination path. If the destination is an existing directory, the source will be copied inside it.

Usage:
filecopy <source> <destination>

Examples:
filecopy file.txt /home/user/Documents
filecopy file.txt file2.txt
filecopy # Error: Invalid source or destination provided.
